We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to instruct the GSO to:

immediately work out for the issuance of red plates by the LTO for the 9 vehicles with conduction stickers and 16 motorcycles without plate numbers and install the same in front and at the rear of every vehicle/motorcycle;



work out for the conversion of one vehicle with a private plate into red plate; 



cause for the proper markings of all vehicles/motorcycles owned by the municipality as prescribed in COA Circular No. 77-61 to prevent unauthorized or improper use thereof, and



cause for the immediate registration of the vehicles/motorcycles with LTO and henceforth see to it that such registration is renewed before the expiration date.

To correct the aforementioned deficiencies, we recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:

instruct all the heads of offices to fill out all the data in the PR and indicate the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being requested to be purchased and avoid indicating the brand name except for replacement of parts; 
instruct the GSO Designate to see to it that all the data in the RFQ/Canvass Paper are completely filled out and that the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being canvassed are indicated therein except the brand name unless the items are replacements of parts;

instruct the GSO Designate to require the bidders to indicate in the RFQ/Bill of Quantities the brand name of items they are quoting which shall be incorporated in the PO;

instruct the GSO Designate to see to it that all data in the PO are completely filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items being ordered are indicated therein including the brand name of the items as indicated by the winning bidder in the RFQ/Canvass Paper/Bill of Quantities;

instruct the   Agency Inspector and the GSO Designate   who sign the inspection and acceptance portions of the AIR respectively that such document is properly filled out and the exact unit of measure and complete specifications of items accepted and inspected including the brand name of the items be indicated therein;

require the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Engineer and the BAC to submit the lacking documents of infrastructure projects with aggregate cost of   ₱92,889,710.49 to avoid the issuance of Notices of Suspensions;

require the Municipal Accountant and the head of office in charge for the distribution of goods with aggregate cost of ₱7,324,500.00 to submit the Distribution Lists, otherwise, these transactions shall be suspended in audit;

require the head of office in charge in the distribution of goods for the under-distribution with equivalent amount of ₱84,900.00 to submit an explanation for this deficiency;

instruct the Municipal Accountant and the head of office in charge in the distribution of goods that henceforth, see to it that such are supported with Pre-Master List of Beneficiaries, pictures of the goods to be distributed, duly accomplished Distribution Lists indicating among others the title and date of activity, the name and address of recipients, the quantity and complete specifications of items distributed, signature of recipients and certification of the head of office that the Distribution Lists are true and correct and pictures during distribution.

require the GSO Designate to submit PAR for the issuances of non-expendable properties aggregating ₱5,665,590.00;


require the GSO Designate to submit ICS for issuances of semi-expendable properties aggregating ₱1,711,355.65;

require the BAC to submit a photo copy of the Notices of Award as bases for claiming their honoraria in the amount of ₱526,230.00;

require the Municipal Accountant to issue a certification that the previous cash advance of the payee has been liquidated before processing payment for another cash advance;  

require the Municipal Accountant to see to it that cash advances for payroll are supported with payroll duly signed by the signatories indicated in Boxes A to D therein without the signatures of the payees, as basis of the amount to be cash advanced;

require the head of office in charge of the activity for which meals and/or snacks shall be served to participants or visitors to see to it that these are supported with duly accomplished Attendance Sheet indicating the date and title of the activity, the name and signatures of participants, pictures taken during the activity and pictures showing that the participants are taking their meals/snacks;

require the GSO Designate to see to it that Delivery Receipts are dated and the Municipal Treasurer to make sure that the Sales Invoices and Official/Collection Receipts are dated before releasing payments to suppliers/contractors, and

require the Municipal Accountant that henceforth, see to it that disbursements are supported with complete documentation.

a) Carefully scrutinize the account numbers written in the deposit slip before depositing to the bank to ensure that the correct account where the funds are supposed to be deposited will be credited pursuant to Section 125 of GAM for LGUs Vol. 1;
b) Regularly request a copy of the bank statements or snapshots to check whether the deposits, disbursements and other transactions reflected therein pertain to the LGU; and
c) Effect the transfer of the subject funds to the Trust Fund bank account.

a. The Municipal Accountant in coordination with the Municipal Budget Officer to reconcile at year-end their respective records/registries after taking considerations any material adjustments particularly on the discrepancy of actual and estimated revenue which affects DRRMF allocation, in order to properly and accurately determine the amount of unexpended LDRRM Fund;
b. The Municipal Accountant to make the necessary accounting entry to record the transfer of the unexpended balance to the Trust Liabilities – DRRMF;
c. The Officers’ concerned to follow the procedures in the utilization of unexpended DRRM Fund as prescribed in item 6.5 of NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1; and
d. The Municipal Budget Officer to present only those unimplemented Capital Outlay Appropriations as Continuing Appropriations in its Status of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations.

We recommended that the LCE:

Require the Municipal Accountant and concerned officials strict compliance with Section 4 (6) of PD 1445 and pertinent provisions of COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; 

Instruct the concerned officials to submit the lacking documents to the Municipal Accountant who will verify the completeness and accuracy thereof and subsequently submit the same to the Auditor in order for the latter to verify the validity, propriety and correctness of these documents and compliance of said transactions with the abovementioned provisions of law and regulations.

We recommended that the LCE: 

Enforce a centralized system on the procurement of supplies, materials and equipment for proper control on the acquisition and issuances thereof wherein the GSO/Municipal Treasurer will determine the items to be procured based on the Consolidated Annual Procurement Plan of the Municipality and require the BAC to conduct a public bidding for items not available in the Procurement Service (PS)-DBM; 
Require the Office of the GSO/Municipal Treasurer to take charge on the preparation of voucher, purchase request, purchase order and other supporting documents pertaining to the procurement of supplies, materials and equipment;
Adhere strictly with the Letter of Instructions No. 755, Executive Order Nos. 289 series of 1987, 359 series of 1989, and 322 series of 2000, using the Electronic Procurement System by procuring commonly used supplies, materials and equipment from the PS- DBM; 

Require the GSO/Municipal Treasurer to submit the Acceptance and Inspection Report of all consumables to the Auditor within twenty-four (24) hours from delivery; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to record purchases of supplies and materials to be carried in stock as inventory regardless of whether or not they are consumed within the accounting period following the perpetual inventory method.

