We recommended that Municipal Mayor:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to verify their records relative to the status of the foregoing outstanding checks which might have already been replaced;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjustments in the books and furnish a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher to the Municipal Treasurer as her basis in adjusting the cashbooks;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to record the reconciling items in her cashbook to reflect the correct balances; and
Instruct both the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile their records regularly to immediately make any adjustments affecting both records to show accurate and reliable balances.

We recommended that Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Accountant:
Locate source documents of the transactions included in the Accounts Payable account and inform the suppliers to present their corresponding claims duly supported with the required documents for processing and payment thereof;
Locate and review the source transactions of the loans and premium payments included in the Due to GSIS, Philhealth and Pagibig accounts and identify the personnel whose salaries were deducted with the subject loan payment and premium contributions so that subsequent remittances thereof will be appropriately posted/reflected to the paying member;
Locate the source documents and MOA/Trust Agreements with the source agencies and review the terms and conditions relative to the implementation of programs and projects.  Determine the viability of the usage of funds and if the same could still be used for other projects, seek the approval of the source agencies if deemed necessary;
Return/remit to the source agency any unused/unexpended balance if so stipulated in the MOA/Trust Agreement in order to reflect the correct balance of the account in the financial statements;
Effect the transfer of funds which are due to other funds and prepare adjusting entries of long outstanding accounts; and
Furnish COA with the JEV effecting the adjusting/correcting entries relative to the foregoing.

We recommended that Management:
prioritize the implementation of projects which are aligned to the allowable usages of shares from tobacco excise tax as provided under Section 2 of Republic Act No. 7171; and
refrain from funding projects which do not provide developmental impact to tobacco farmers or the industry to the effect that subsequent construction of school  building shall be charged against the appropriation for capital outlay under Special Education Fund;

